The `read()` call is now moved to the beginning of the loop, eliminating the need to repeat it at the end of the loop. This ensures that new data is read from `src_fd` before each iteration.

Other than these changes, the functionality of the function remains the same. It reads data from `src_fd` in chunks and sends it to `dst_fd` using `http_send_data()`, until the end of file is reached.

int http_send_data(int fd, char *data, size_t size) {
    ssize_t bytes_sent;
    while (size > 0) {
        bytes_sent = write(fd, data, size);
        if (bytes_sent < 0)
            return bytes_sent;
        size -= bytes_sent;
        data += bytes_sent;
    }
    return 0;
}

